.row
  .large-7.columns
    h1 Download
    p 
      'The easiest way to get started using InfluxDB is to head over to 
      a href="http://play.influxdb.org" play.influxdb.org
      '  where you can create a database and start writing data and exploring it through the administrative interface in seconds. There's no signup required. It's an open sandbox for you to play in.

    h2 OS X
    p We should have a brew recipe ready in the next week or so.
    / 'OSX users running 10.6 (Snow Leopard) or newer up to 10.9 (Mavericks) can install via 
    / a href="http://brew.sh/" Homebrew
    / '  by running 
    / code brew install influxdb
    / '  from the command line. Follow the post install instructions and InfluxDB will start up automatically for you.

    h2 Ubuntu & Debian
    p Debian users can install by downloading the package and installing it like this:
    pre
      code
        | # for 64 bit systems
          wget http://s3.amazonaws.com/influxdb/influxdb_latest_amd64.deb
          sudo dpkg -i influxdb_latest_amd64.deb

          # for 32 bit systems
          wget http://s3.amazonaws.com/influxdb/influxdb_latest_i386.deb
          sudo dpkg -i influxdb_latest_i386.deb

    h2 RedHat & CentOS
    p RedHat and CentOS users can install by downloading and installing the rpm like this:
    pre
      code
        | # for 64 bit systems
          wget http://s3.amazonaws.com/influxdb/influxdb-latest-1.x86_64.rpm
          sudo rpm -ivh influxdb-latest-1.x86_64.rpm

          # for 32 bit systems
          wget http://s3.amazonaws.com/influxdb/influxdb-latest-1.i686.rpm
          sudo rpm -ivh influxdb-latest-1.i686.rpm

    h2 All Versions
    p Here's a list of all the available builds and versions that we've released.
